I have lived all my life in a fast paced city that never stops. To me, being slow and conscious is a luxury I’ve not  had, until this musical city…

It takes to leave where you’ve been all your life to know what makes you really alive. Rishikesh gave me the warmest hug I really needed.

Living slow doesn’t mean doing nothing or just sitting around. To me, it means filtering out things that protect my peace, and doing that.

It means being grateful to your breathe, 
to each and every element that surrounds you, 
to be in love, stay in love, 
to let the people around you breathe, 
to hold them, 
to lovingly acknowledge them for being whoever they are, 
to be whoever you are…

This is one of the slow, soft and simple mornings of Rishikesh. I fell in love with myself here, again, and with all that nurtures me.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Pyaar Travel Hai
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
4 years ago I wrote a poem to myself! It's called Freedom. 🕊

In the verses of that poem I described how I wanted to see villages, 
and meet new people from all over India. 🌈

I wanted to witness the love, mountains, rivers and hope. 🌊🏔

Right from 11th January 2018, when I wrote down this dream, till today, I have worked towards living this dream. ✨

I visited Malana, Jibhi, Shangarh, and various other places that breathed a new life into my city life. 😍

I have found love in all these corners that I have visited. Also, learnt to unlearn and let go! 🌸

So, on this day of love, all I want to show you is that for me, #PyaarTravelHai | My source of hope, love and friendships! 🥰
